stone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2018-09-07T02:44:40Z", "updated_at": "2018-11-23T18:39:25Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/pulls/22136", "html_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/22136", "diff_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/22136.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/22136.patch"}, "body_html": "<p>When training with MonitoredTrainingSession in distributed mode,<br>\nall ops related with report_uninitialized_xxx will be placed on ps0,<br>\nwhich may lead to OOM when workers up to thousands.</p>\n<p>We use a environment variable to solve it. When OOM happens, users can<br>\nset the local device to fix the problem, such as<br>\nos.environ['TF_LOCAL_DEVICE'] = '/job:worker/task:index'.</p>\n<p><span class=\"issue-keyword tooltipped tooltipped-se\" aria-label=\"This pull request closes issue #22137.\">Fixes</span> <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load issue title\" data-id=\"357902847\" data-permission-text=\"Issue title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/22137\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/22137/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/22137\">#22137</a></p>", "body_text": "When training with MonitoredTrainingSession in distributed mode,\nall ops related with report_uninitialized_xxx will be placed on ps0,\nwhich may lead to OOM when workers up to thousands.\nWe use a environment variable to solve it. When OOM happens, users can\nset the local device to fix the problem, such as\nos.environ['TF_LOCAL_DEVICE'] = '/job:worker/task:index'.\nFixes #22137", "body": "When training with MonitoredTrainingSession in distributed mode,\r\nall ops related with report_uninitialized_xxx will be placed on ps0,\r\nwhich may lead to OOM when workers up to thousands.\r\n\r\nWe use a environment variable to solve it. When OOM happens, users can\r\nset the local device to fix the problem, such as\r\nos.environ['TF_LOCAL_DEVICE'] = '/job:worker/task:index'.\r\n\r\nFixes #22137"}